<% content_for :title, "Privacy — Printwright" %>
<div class="container" style="max-width: 720px">
  <h1>Privacy</h1>
  <p class="t-small muted"><strong>Template, not legal advice.</strong> Last updated 2026-07-17.</p>

  <h2>What we store</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Designers:</strong> email address, display name, password hash, and the
      Hedera account id you give us for payouts.</li>
    <li><strong>Buyers:</strong> no account. A purchase stores the paying Hedera account
      id (public on-chain anyway), the payment transaction id, and the license issued. If you
      explicitly opt into the license library from a paid receipt, we also store the email address
      you provide so we can send private library links; it is not published on-chain.</li>
    <li><strong>On-chain:</strong> license certificates (model hash, license type, unit
      serial, buyer account hint, payment tx, terms hash) are published permanently to a
      public Hedera Consensus Service topic — that is the product. Do not buy a license
      from an account you do not want publicly associated with the purchase.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>No advertising, no tracking pixels, no sale of data.</li>
    <li>No analytics beyond server logs (rotated) needed to run the service.</li>
    <li>Private keys never touch our servers — payments are signed client-side.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Removal</h2>
  <p>Email us to delete a designer account or optional buyer-library email; database records go,
    on-chain certificates are permanent by design. Questions: see the repository README for contact.</p>
</div>
